## LLM rules

LLM features are used. Models:
- `gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview` — video frame extraction + knowledge answers + batch indexing (Cloud Run Python)
- `gemini-3-flash-preview` — Vietnamese synthesis output (Cloud Run Python)
- `gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview` — intent classification fallback (Vercel Edge Runtime, < 5% of queries)
- `gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview` — follow-up text responses (Vercel Edge Runtime)

Cost ceiling: $70/month across all Gemini usage (batch + user queries).

Never reference Gemini 2.5 (shutdown June 17, 2026) or Gemini 2.0 (shutdown March 31, 2026). Use Gemini 3.x only.

AI inference location:
- Video analysis (①③④): Cloud Run Python service — `GEMINI_API_KEY` in Cloud Run env only
- Text intents (⑤⑥⑦ + follow-ups): Vercel Edge Runtime — `GEMINI_API_KEY` in Vercel env secret only
- Batch indexing: Cloud Run batch service
- API keys never in frontend bundle

## AI module boundary

- All AI wrapper modules for the frontend live in `src/lib/` (e.g., `src/lib/niche-resolver.ts`)
- Components and hooks never call AI SDKs directly — always through wrapper modules or via Supabase Edge Function / Cloud Run SSE endpoint
- Cloud Run Python pipeline lives in `cloud-run/getviews_pipeline/` — forked from GetReels-MCP, adapted for Vietnamese context and Supabase corpus
- AI modules receive niche, corpus data, and user context as function arguments — never import app-specific config
- Frontend → Cloud Run: direct SSE with Supabase JWT in Authorization header
- Frontend → Vercel Edge: `/api/chat` endpoint (text intents only)

## Key constraints

- All Gemini API keys are server-only — never in the frontend bundle (`VITE_` prefix forbidden for Gemini keys)
- Atomic credit deduction via Supabase RPC `decrement_credit()` — WHERE guard prevents overdraft (TD-1)
- PayOS webhook idempotency via `processed_webhook_events` UNIQUE constraint — retries safe (TD-2)
- Concurrent request guard: `profiles.is_processing` boolean — cron resets stale flags after 5 minutes (TD-3)
- SSE reconnection: `stream_id` + `seq` per token — Cloud Run replays from 60s in-memory buffer (TD-4)
- Credits granted upfront at PAID webhook — no monthly top-up cron (TD-5). PayOS is one-time.
- Facebook OAuth is non-negotiable for the Vietnamese market — do not remove or deprioritize
- Vietnamese language throughout all UI copy — no English strings in user-facing UI
- Mobile-first viewport: 360–393px baseline, 44×44px minimum touch targets
- R2 buckets (`getviews-frames`, `getviews-videos`) are public — no signed URLs needed (public TikTok content thumbnails/clips)
- Chat messages are immutable — no UPDATE on `chat_messages`; use soft-delete on sessions via `deleted_at`
- `video_corpus` INSERT is batch-only (service role via Cloud Run) — RLS blocks client writes
- ZaloPay in Figma Make PricingScreen — confirm PayOS integration supports it before launching

